📌 What is Ansible?

Ansible is an open-source configuration management and deployment tool used to:

Install software
Update applications
Remove packages
Create/delete users
Automate infrastructure
👉 It is widely used in DevOps for automation and CI/CD pipelines

🔥 Configuration Management Tools
Tool	Agent	Type
Chef	Required	Pull-based
Puppet	Required	Pull-based
Ansible	Not Required	Push-based

👉 Key Difference:

Chef & Puppet → Agents installed on servers
Ansible → No agent required (uses SSH)
⚙️ Key Features of Ansible
Agentless architecture
Uses SSH for communication
Simple YAML syntax (easy to learn)
Idempotent (safe to run multiple times)
Fast and lightweight
Secure (no additional ports required)
🧩 What Can Ansible Do?

👉 Ansible can:

Install software on single/multiple systems
Configure servers automatically
Deploy applications
Manage users and permissions
Perform patch updates
Orchestrate multi-tier applications
🧠 Ansible Architecture
Ansible Control Node (Server)
        |
        | SSH
        ↓
Managed Nodes (Host Servers)
🔹 Components of Ansible
1. Control Node (Ansible Server)

👉 The machine where Ansible is installed
👉 Executes playbooks

2. Managed Nodes (Host Servers)

👉 Target systems where tasks are executed

3. Inventory (Hosts File)

👉 Contains list of servers

Example:

[dev]
172.31.37.28
172.31.35.4
4. Playbook

👉 YAML file that defines tasks

Example:

- hosts: dev
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: Install Nginx
      apt:
        name: nginx
        state: present
5. Modules

👉 Pre-built tools used to perform tasks

Examples:

ping
apt
yum
copy
service
6. Tasks

👉 Individual actions in playbook

7. Roles

👉 Organize playbooks into reusable structure

🔥 Important Terminology
Term	    Meaning
Inventory	List of servers
Playbook	YAML automation file
Task	    Single action
Module	    Tool used in task
Role	    Structured automation
Handler	    Runs when notified
Variables	Store dynamic values

⚡ Push vs Pull Model
🔹 Push Model (Ansible)
Control node pushes configuration
No agent needed
🔹 Pull Model (Chef/Puppet)
Agents pull configuration from server
💯 Real-Time Example

👉 In project:

Install Java & Maven
Deploy Spring Boot application
Configure server
Restart services
🎯 Interview Answer (Best)

“Ansible is an open-source configuration management and deployment tool used to automate tasks like software installation, server configuration, and application deployment. It is agentless and uses SSH to push configurations from the control node to managed nodes using YAML-based playbooks.”

🚀 Summary
Tool Type → Automation
Architecture → Agentless
Communication → SSH
Language → YAML
Model → Push-based